title: Miwa Yonetsu
text:
is a former <a href="Japan">Japan</a>ese <a href="Association%20football">football</a> player. She played for <a href="Japan%20women%27s%20national%20football%20team">Japan national team</a>.
Club career.
Yonetsu was born in <a href="Osaka%20Prefecture">Osaka Prefecture</a> on December 4, 1979. After graduating from <a href="Himeji%20Gakuin%20Women%27s%20Junior%20College">Himeji Gakuin Women's Junior College</a>, she joined her local club <a href="Toyotsu%20Ladies%20FC">Toyotsu Ladies FC</a> in 2000. In 2004, she moved to <a href="L.League">L.League</a> club <a href="INAC%20Kobe%20Leonessa">INAC Leonessa</a> (later "INAC Kobe Leonessa"). She retired end of 2011 season.
National team career.
On July 29, 2009, when Yonetsu was 29 years old, she debuted for <a href="Japan%20women%27s%20national%20football%20team">Japan national team</a> against <a href="Germany%20women%27s%20national%20football%20team">Germany</a>. She played 2 games for Japan in 2009.
